text.section:
A leaseholder shall:
Subject to subsection (b) of this section, actively use the lease and comply with any standards for planting, harvesting, and use of the leased area established by the Department;
Mark each lease area with an 8-inch by 12-inch marker displaying the initials of the leaseholder and posted on a minimum of four poles;
Comply with any other marking requirements established by the Department for the protection of navigation;
Comply with the regulations established by the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene in consultation with the Department of the Environment to carry out the mandate of the National Shellfish Sanitation Program; and
Pay the rent and the aquaculture development surcharge for the lease at the time established by the Department.

A leaseholder may not:
Place shellfish, bags, nets, or structures on submerged aquatic vegetation;
Plant or harvest shellfish within 500 yards of any stationary blind or blind site that is occupied and being used for hunting migratory waterfowl;
Sublease a lease;
Transfer a lease without the approval of the Department;
Harvest shellfish between the hours of sunset and sunrise; or
Place unlawfully harvested oysters on a lease.
